ABOUT THE CODE:
This is the first assignment of the of the Computational Metallurgy Lab (MM3421).
This assignment contains rudimentary exercise for converting the cartesian coordinates
into polar coordinates and plotting a simple circle (of any convenient radius).

OBJECTIVES:
1. To get fimiliarized with computer programming and solving scientific problems using
   computers.
2. To get fimiliarized with OCTAVE/MATLAB language.  


EXECUTION OF THE C CODE:
(For Ubuntu 20.04 LTS)
	
To run the code manually:
1. Compile the C code "circle2D.c" using a suitable compiler (gcc most preferentially).
2. Execute "gnuplot" command (install gnuplot from apt-get terminal command if not installed).
3. execute command: "load circle2D.plt".

To run the the code automatically:
1. execute the command: "chmod +x circle_program.sh".
2. execute the command: "./circle_program.sh".

EXECUTION OF THE OCTAVE CODE:

1. Execute the "octave" command or open the Octave GUI software.
2. Execute the "run circle2D.m" command from the Octave prompt.   
